            <div class="opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper ">

    
    <h1 class="opener__hed " >        Life in Limbo: Victims of New Mexico’s Biggest Wildfire Wait for Checks From the Federal Government to Rebuild
    </h1>

    <h2 class="opener__dek " >        Congress set aside $4 billion to compensate victims after the U.S. Forest Service accidentally set the largest wildfire in state history. The vast majority of victims haven’t been paid, and many can’t rebuild until they are.
    </h2>

    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

</div>
        
<div class="article-meta-1
     article-meta-1--left     " data-pp-location="article meta">

    <span class="article-meta-1__byline" data-pp-location="article byine">
        by <span class="name">Patrick Lohmann</span>, <a href="https://sourcenm.com/">Source New Mexico</a>, and <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/byard-duncan">Byard Duncan</a>, ProPublica    </span>
    <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
        <time class="timestamp" datetime="2023-09-28EDT05:00">Sept. 28, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
    </time>

    <div class="article-meta-1__section-actions
