<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="4.0">The tour confirmed what satellite imagery hinted at: This 97-acre property was a total loss. The home Naranjo and his wife had shared for 50 years, a stand of aspen trees, a small apple orchard, miles of fencing and a bridge he had built himself, all gone.</p>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="5.0">Naranjo, 86, hasn’t laid the first adobe brick of a replacement home, hammered a fence post or planted a single tree. And with congestive heart failure raising the risk of a stroke, he worries he won’t live long enough to do so.</p>
        
    
                        

